	 - From TAT: The African Times news article provides details that support the claim that James Johnson's influence extended beyond the church into political matters. It specifically mentions that Administrator (now Governor) Moloney nominated him as a member of the Legislative Council in Lagos, which aligns with the claim. This nomination earned him the title of "Honourable," indicating his involvement in political affairs. Additionally, the article highlights his role as a spokesman for a deputation on "Education" that met with the Governor in Lagos, further demonstrating his engagement in civic matters. These details corroborate the claim that Johnson's influence was not confined to religious circles but also encompassed political involvement.


